Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C and bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with a 
pinch of @salt{pinch}. Slice the @potatoes{450%g} into 1cm thick rounds (no need to peel). 
Add to the boiling water and simmer until tender, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> TIP: The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through. Once cooked, 
carefully drain in a #colander{} (don't worry if it breaks up a bit!).

Meanwhile, trim the @carrots{3}, then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into 
roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons. Pop the carrot on a #baking tray{} and drizzle with 
@olive oil{2%tbsp} and season with a pinch of salt and @ground black pepper{pinch}. 
Drizzle over the @honey{15%ml} and toss to coat. Leave the tray to the side.

Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(finely chopped) (stalks and all) and pop 
half of it in a #small bowl{} with the @panko breadcrumbs{30%g} along with a quarter 
of the @grated hard Italian style cheese{40%g}. Add the oil and a pinch of salt and 
pepper. Mix together and leave to the side. Pop the carrots on the middle shelf of 
your oven to roast until golden and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through 
cooking.

Put the @creme fraiche{200%g} in a large #bowl{} and stir in the @water{50%ml}, 
remaining cheese and parsley and a pinch of salt and pepper. Mix together. Arrange 
half the drained potatoes in a small/medium #ovenproof dish{} (depending on how many 
people you are cooking for). Pour over half of the crème fraîche mixture to cover the 
potato. Add the rest of the potato and top with the remaining crème fraîche mixture.

Place the @whiting fillet{4} on top (skin-side down) of the creamy potatoes. Evenly 
sprinkle over the crumb mixture and bake on the top shelf of your oven until the crumbs 
are golden and the fish cooked, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: the fish is cooked when opaque all the way through.

While everything bakes, get your washing up done! Once everything is cooked, serve the 
creamy fish and potato gratin on plates with the roasted carrots on the side. 
Enjoy!